sec.p:
We hypothesise that, in comparison with usual care, the Tel + SMS intervention will improve the following main outcomes:
lower child BMI at age 3 years;
lower child screen time (i.e. TV viewing time) and increased physical activity;
better dietary quality (i.e. greater intake of fruits/vegetables) at 3 years;
improved mothers’ healthy eating and physical activity; and
demonstrated cost-effectiveness of the intervention.
